    },
    {
      "id": 2,
      "text": "On November 7, 1921, residents voted unanimously to incorporate Kensington as a village, formalizing its local government.",
      "sourceSentenceIds": [
        5,
        9
      ],
      "sourceLabels": [
        "Web source 1",
        "Wikipedia"
      ],
      "source": "https://vok-ny.com/about/"
    },
    {
      "id": 3,
      "text": "In August 1915, the village’s waterfront park was deeded to the Kensington Association, preserving a public green space.",
      "sourceSentenceIds": [
        11
      ],
      "sourceLabels": [
        "Wikipedia"
      ],
      "source": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Kensington%2C_New_York"
    },
    {
      "id": 4,
      "text": "A restrictive covenant was written early on to keep business and industry out, preserving Kensington’s residential character.",
      "sourceSentenceIds": [
        12
      ],
      "sourceLabels": [
        "Wikipedia"
      ],
      "source": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Kensington%2C_New_York"
    },
    {
      "id": 5,
      "text": "Kensington has long been recognized as one of the safest places to live in the United States.",
      "sourceSentenceIds": [
        14
      ],
      "sourceLabels": [
        "Wikipedia"
      ],
      "source": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Kensington%2C_New_York"
    },
    {
      "id": 6,
      "text": "In 2017, Niche.com ranked Kensington #1 among New York’s best places to live and best suburbs to live in.",
